#read in data
yield <- read_csv("geraniums.csv")
## Rows: 16 Columns: 3
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (2): sunlight, water
## dbl (1): yield
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
#convert to factors
yield <- yield %>% mutate(sunlight = factor(sunlight)) %>% mutate(water = factor(water))
#sunlight boxplot
ggplot(data = yield, aes(x = sunlight, y = yield))+
  geom_boxplot()

#sunlight statistics
favstats(yield~sunlight, data = yield)
##   sunlight min    Q1 median   Q3 max   mean        sd n missing
## 1     High  14 15.75   18.5 22.5  33 20.625  7.049569 8       0
## 2      Low   4  6.75   10.0 20.5  40 14.875 12.147163 8       0
#water boxplot
ggplot(data = yield, aes(x = water, y = yield))+
  geom_boxplot()

#water statistics
favstats(yield~water, data = yield)
##   water min    Q1 median    Q3 max  mean       sd n missing
## 1  High   4  6.75   11.5 18.25  33 13.75 9.765098 8       0
## 2   Low  13 14.75   20.0 24.00  40 21.75 9.176834 8       0
#interaction plot
yield_sum <- yield %>% 
  group_by(sunlight, water) %>% 
  summarise(mean_yield = mean(yield))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'sunlight'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
ggplot(data=yield_sum,aes(x=sunlight, mean_yield)) +
  geom_line(aes(group=water, color=water)) +
  geom_point(aes(color=water))

#combined statistics
favstats(yield~sunlight+water, data = yield)

## 4        Low.Low  13 18.25   21.0 26.5  40 23.75 11.500000 4       0

yield_means_water <- emmeans(yield_log,~sunlight|water)
